{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884471535,"sessionID":"ses_28509b942ffeo3dSThXccTyRCR","part":{"id":"prt_d7af68833001NgKOvJ9cm2SM54","messageID":"msg_d7af6706c001Dylh5ijAgaI6My","sessionID":"ses_28509b942ffeo3dSThXccTyRCR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_20836cf1f8b04c91bd7ed3d7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for testing the Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) and its CLI functionality.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-040\n10: - **Module**: `sdk-python/tests`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ## Reference\n15: \n16: Base specs from:\n17: - `python-sdk/design.md` - SDK design and architecture\n18: - `python-sdk/spec.md` - Functional requirements\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Background\n23: \n24: The Python SDK provides two main client classes:\n25: - `CodeInterpreterClient`: Manages Code Interpreter sessions via Workload Manager (control plane) and Router (data plane)\n26: - `AgentRuntimeClient`: Invokes AgentRuntime workloads through the Router\n27: \n28: The SDK also includes utility modules and exception classes.\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## Requirements\n33: \n34: ### Feature: CodeInterpreterClient Lifecycle\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: AR-040-001-A — Client initialization with all parameters\n37: \n38: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with explicit values for all parameters\n39: - **WHEN** `__init__` runs\n40: - **THEN** the instance SHALL have `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `router_url`, `auth_token`, `verbose`, and `session_id` set to the provided values\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-040-001-B — Client initialization with defaults\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with no arguments\n45: - **WHEN** `__init__` runs\n46: - **THEN** `name` SHALL be `\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace` SHALL be `\"default\"`, `ttl` SHALL be `3600`, and `verbose` SHALL be `False`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: AR-040-001-C — Router URL from environment variable\n49: \n50: - **GIVEN** environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set to `\"http://router.example.com\"`\n51: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated without `router_url` argument\n52: - **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL equal `\"http://router.example.com\"`\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-040-001-D — Router URL missing raises error\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n57: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n58: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: AR-040-001-E — Context manager entry creates session\n61: \n62: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is valid and control plane is reachable\n63: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` enters context manager (`__enter__`)\n64: - **THEN** `create_session` SHALL be called on the control plane client\n65: - **AND** `session_id` SHALL be populated on the instance\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: AR-040-001-F — Context manager exit cleans up on success\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` was created with a new session (not provided)\n70: - **WHEN** the context block exits without exception\n71: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` to delete the session\n72: - **AND** close both control plane and data plane clients\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: AR-040-001-G — Context manager exit cleans up on exception\n75: \n76: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` was created with a new session\n77: - **WHEN** an exception is raised inside the context block\n78: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL still call `stop()` to clean up resources\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: AR-040-001-H — Data plane init failure cleans up session\n81: \n82: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n83: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n84: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning\n85: - **AND** call `delete_session(session_id)`\n86: - **AND** set `session_id` to `None`\n87: - **AND** re-raise the exception\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ### Feature: CodeInterpreterClient Operations\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: AR-040-002-A — Execute command delegates to data plane\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` has a valid `dp_client` (data plane)\n96: - **WHEN** `execute_command(\"ls -la\")` is called\n97: - **THEN** it SHALL delegate to `self.dp_client.execute_command()`\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: AR-040-002-B — Execute command with custom timeout\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` with default timeout 120\n102: - **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo test\", timeout=60)` is called\n103: - **THEN** the request SHALL use 60-second timeout\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: AR-040-002-C — Run code for Python writes file and executes\n106: \n107: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance\n108: - **WHEN** `run_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\")` is called\n109: - **THEN** it SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file`\n110: - **AND** execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: AR-040-002-D — Run code normalizes language variants\n113: \n114: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance\n115: - **WHEN** `run_code(\"py\", \"code\")` is called (language \"py\")\n116: - **THEN** it SHALL treat it the same as \"python\"\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: AR-040-002-E — File operations delegate to data plane\n119: \n120: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` has a valid `dp_client`\n121: - **WHEN** `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, or `list_files` is called\n122: - **THEN** each SHALL delegate to the corresponding `dp_client` method\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ### Feature: ControlPlaneClient Configuration\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: AR-040-003-A — Control plane URL from argument\n129: \n130: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url=\"http://wm.example.com\"` is passed\n131: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n132: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal `\"http://wm.example.com\"`\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: AR-040-003-B — Control plane URL from environment\n135: \n136: - **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var is set and no argument is passed\n137: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n138: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal the environment variable value\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: AR-040-003-C — Control plane authorization with explicit token\n141: \n142: - **GIVEN** `auth_token=\"my-token\"` is provided\n143: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n144: - **THEN** `self.session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be set to `\"Bearer my-token\"`\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: AR-040-003-D — Control plane authorization from token file\n147: \n148: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided and service account token exists\n149: - **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n150: - **THEN** it SHALL read token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n151: - **AND** set `Authorization: Bearer {token_content}` header\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: AR-040-003-E — Control plane default timeout values\n154: \n155: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is instantiated without timeout arguments\n156: - **WHEN** the client is examined\n157: - **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120`\n158: - **AND** `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n159: - **AND** `self.pool_connections` SHALL be `10`\n160: - **AND** `self.pool_maxsize` SHALL be `10`\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ### Feature: ControlPlaneClient Operations\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: AR-040-004-A — Create session POSTs to correct endpoint\n167: \n168: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` with `base_url=\"http://wm.example.com\"`\n169: - **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=3600)` is called\n170: - **THEN** it SHALL POST to `http://wm.example.com/v1/code-interpreter`\n171: - **AND** JSON body SHALL contain `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`\n172: - **AND** return the `sessionId` from response\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: AR-040-004-B — Create session with metadata\n175: \n176: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient`\n177: - **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", metadata={\"key\": \"value\"}, ttl=3600)` is called\n178: - **THEN** the JSON body SHALL include `metadata` field\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: AR-040-004-C — Create session missing sessionId raises\n181: \n182: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` and successful HTTP response without `sessionId`\n183: - **WHEN** `create_session` processes the response\n184: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError`\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: AR-040-004-D — Delete session returns True on 404\n187: \n188: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient`\n189: - **WHEN** `delete_session(\"non-existent-id\")` is called\n190: - **AND** server returns HTTP 404\n191: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: AR-040-004-E — Delete session returns False on other errors\n194: \n195: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient`\n196: - **WHEN** `delete_session(\"some-id\")` is called\n197: - **AND** server returns HTTP 500\n198: - **THEN** the method SHALL log the error\n199: - **AND** return `False`\n200: \n201: ---\n202: \n203: ### Feature: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient URL Construction\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: AR-040-005-A — Data plane URL from router components\n206: \n207: - **GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"test-ns\"`, `cr_name=\"my-cr\"`\n208: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` initializes without `base_url`\n209: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal `\"http://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/test-ns/code-interpreters/my-cr/invocations/\"`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: AR-040-005-B — Data plane URL uses explicit base_url\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** `base_url=\"http://explicit.example.com/v1/...\"`\n214: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` initializes\n215: - **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal the provided `base_url`\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ### Feature: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient File Operations\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: AR-040-006-A — write_file sends base64 content\n222: \n223: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with valid session\n224: - **WHEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n225: - **THEN** a POST request SHALL be made to `api/files`\n226: - **AND** JSON body SHALL contain base64-encoded `content`, `path`, and `mode: \"0644\"`\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: AR-040-006-B — upload_file sends multipart request\n229: \n230: - **GIVEN** a temporary file exists at `/tmp/upload_test.txt`\n231: - **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/tmp/upload_test.txt\", remote_path=\"/tmp/dest.txt\")` is called\n232: - **THEN** a multipart POST request SHALL be made to `api/files`\n233: - **AND** the request SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: AR-040-006-C — download_file streams response\n236: \n237: - **GIVEN** a file exists on the remote at `/tmp/remote.txt`\n238: - **WHEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/tmp/remote.txt\", local_path=\"/tmp/local.txt\")` is called\n239: - **THEN** a GET request SHALL be made to `api/files/remote.txt`\n240: - **AND** `stream=True` SHALL be used\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: AR-040-006-D — list_files queries directory\n243: \n244: - **GIVEN** a directory `/code` exists on the remote\n245: - **WHEN** `list_files(path=\"/code\")` is called\n246: - **THEN** a GET request SHALL be made to `api/files?path=%2Fcode`\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ### Feature: AgentRuntimeClient Session Bootstrap\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: AR-040-007-A — AgentRuntimeClient initializes with parameters\n253: \n254: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated\n255: - **WHEN** `__init__` runs\n256: - **THEN** instance SHALL have `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `router_url` set\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: AR-040-007-B — Session ID extracted from response header\n259: \n260: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` makes GET request to invocation URL\n261: - **WHEN** the response includes header `x-agentcube-session-id: abc-123`\n262: - **THEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` SHALL return `\"abc-123\"`\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: AR-040-007-C — Missing session header raises error\n265: \n266: - **GIVEN** the GET request returns without `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n267: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n268: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n269: \n270: #### Scenario: AR-040-007-D — Context manager cleanup\n271: \n272: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as context manager\n273: - **WHEN** the block exits\n274: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ### Feature: AgentRuntimeClient Invoke\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: AR-040-008-A — Invoke without session raises\n281: \n282: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty\n283: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"query\": \"test\"})` is called\n284: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: AR-040-008-B — Invoke sends JSON payload\n287: \n288: - **GIVEN** a valid session_id is set\n289: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"query\": \"test\"})` is called\n290: - **THEN** a POST request SHALL be made to the invocation URL\n291: - **AND** `Content-Type: application/json` header SHALL be set\n292: - **AND** body SHALL contain the payload as JSON\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: AR-040-008-C — Invoke uses timeout tuple\n295: \n296: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0`\n297: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload={...})` is called without timeout argument\n298: - **THEN** the request SHALL use timeout `(5.0, 120)`\n299: \n300: #### Scenario: AR-040-008-D — Invoke with per-call timeout override\n301: \n302: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with default timeout 120\n303: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload={...}, timeout=60)` is called\n304: - **THEN** the request SHALL use timeout `(connect_timeout, 60)`\n305: \n306: ---\n307: \n308: ### Feature: Exception Handling\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: AR-040-009-A — CommandExecutionError contains details\n311: \n312: - **GIVEN** a command returns exit code `1` with stderr `\"command not found\"`\n313: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n314: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError`\n315: - **AND** `exit_code` attribute SHALL be `1`\n316: - **AND** `stderr` attribute SHALL be `\"command not found\"`\n317: - **AND** `command` attribute SHALL contain the executed command\n318: \n319: #### Scenario: AR-040-009-B — Exception classes are importable from root\n320: \n321: - **GIVEN** the `agentcube` package is installed\n322: - **WHEN** `from agentcube import AgentCubeError, CommandExecutionError, SessionError, DataPlaneError` is executed\n323: - **THEN** all exception classes SHALL be accessible\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: AR-040-009-C — Exception classes in exceptions module\n326: \n327: - **GIVEN** `agentcube.exceptions` is imported\n328: - **WHEN** the module is examined\n329: - **THEN** `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` SHALL be defined\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ### Feature: Utility Functions\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: AR-040-010-A — create_session returns requests.Session\n336: \n337: - **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called\n338: - **WHEN** the function completes\n339: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` object\n340: - **AND** `HTTPAdapter` SHALL be mounted for http and https\n341: \n342: #### Scenario: AR-040-010-B — read_token_from_file handles missing file\n343: \n344: - **GIVEN** a file path that does not exist\n345: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/path\")` is called\n346: - **THEN** it SHALL return an empty string `\"\"`\n347: - **AND** NOT raise an exception\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: AR-040-010-C — read_token_from_file returns stripped content\n350: \n351: - **GIVEN** a file exists at `/tmp/token` with content `\"  my-token\\n\"`\n352: - **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/token\")` is called\n353: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-token\"` (whitespace stripped)\n354: \n355: #### Scenario: AR-040-010-D — get_logger returns Logger instance\n356: \n357: - **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"test_logger\")` is called\n358: - **WHEN** the function completes\n359: - **THEN** it SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance\n360: - **AND** logger name SHALL be `\"test_logger\"`\n361: \n362: ---\n363: \n364: ### Feature: Public API Surface\n365: \n366: #### Scenario: AR-040-011-A — Root package exports CodeInterpreterClient\n367: \n368: - **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is imported\n369: - **WHEN** `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient` is executed\n370: - **THEN** it SHALL succeed\n371: \n372: #### Scenario: AR-040-011-B — Root package exports AgentRuntimeClient\n373: \n374: - **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is imported\n375: - **WHEN** `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient` is executed\n376: - **THEN** it SHALL succeed\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: AR-040-011-C — Root package __all__ contents\n379: \n380: - **GIVEN** the `agentcube` package\n381: - **WHEN** `agentcube.__all__` is accessed\n382: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n383: \n384: #### Scenario: AR-040-011-D — clients subpackage exports\n385: \n386: - **GIVEN** `agentcube.clients` is imported\n387: - **WHEN** `__all__` is accessed\n388: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `[\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## Acceptance Criteria\n393: \n394: - [ ] AC001: CodeInterpreterClient initializes with correct default values\n395: - [ ] AC002: CodeInterpreterClient reads Router URL from environment when not provided\n396: - [ ] AC003: CodeInterpreterClient raises ValueError when Router URL is missing\n397: - [ ] AC004: CodeInterpreterClient context manager creates and cleans up sessions\n398: - [ ] AC005: CodeInterpreterClient data plane init failure cleans up the created session\n399: - [ ] AC006: CodeInterpreterClient execute_command and run_code delegate to data plane\n400: - [ ] AC007: CodeInterpreterClient run_code handles Python language variants\n401: - [ ] AC008: CodeInterpreterClient file operations delegate to data plane\n402: - [ ] AC009: ControlPlaneClient resolves URL from argument or environment\n403: - [ ] AC010: ControlPlaneClient resolves auth token from argument or token file\n404: - [ ] AC011: ControlPlaneClient create_session POSTs with correct JSON body\n405: - [ ] AC012: ControlPlaneClient delete_session handles 404 as success\n406: - [ ] AC013: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs URL from router components\n407: - [ ] AC014: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient uses explicit base_url when provided\n408: - [ ] AC015: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient write_file sends base64 content\n409: - [ ] AC016: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient upload_file sends multipart request\n410: - [ ] AC017: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient download_file streams response\n411: - [ ] AC018: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient list_files queries with path parameter\n412: - [ ] AC019: AgentRuntimeClient bootstraps session ID from response header\n413: - [ ] AC020: AgentRuntimeClient raises when invoking without session\n414: - [ ] AC021: AgentRuntimeClient invoke sends JSON payload with correct headers\n415: - [ ] AC022: AgentRuntimeClient uses correct timeout tuple\n416: - [ ] AC023: CommandExecutionError contains exit_code, stderr, and command\n417: - [ ] AC024: Exception classes are importable from agentcube root\n418: - [ ] AC025: create_session returns configured requests.Session\n419: - [ ] AC026: read_token_from_file handles missing files gracefully\n420: - [ ] AC027: read_token_from_file returns stripped content\n421: - [ ] AC028: get_logger returns Logger instance with correct name\n422: - [ ] AC029: Public API exports correct classes in __all__\n423: - [ ] AC030: clients subpackage exports correct classes\n424: \n425: ---\n426: \n427: ## Test File Status\n428: \n429: | Source File | Test File | Status |\n430: |-------------|-----------|--------|\n431: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | test_init.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n432: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | test_code_interpreter.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n433: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | test_agent_runtime.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n434: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | test_control_plane.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n435: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n436: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n437: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | test_exceptions.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n438: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | test_http.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n439: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | test_utils.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n440: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | test_log.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n441: \n442: ---\n443: \n444: ## Testing Patterns\n445: \n446: ### Mocking Strategy\n447: - Use `unittest.mock` for mocking HTTP requests and responses\n448: - Use `requests_mock` or similar for HTTP server mocking\n449: - Create fixtures for common client configurations\n450: \n451: ### Test File Naming\n452: - Follow Python convention: `test_*.py`\n453: - Keep tests in `sdk-python/tests/` directory\n454: - Use `pytest` as test runner\n455: \n456: ### Test Fixtures\n457: ```python\n458: @pytest.fixture\n459: def mock_control_plane():\n460:     \"\"\"Fixture for ControlPlaneClient with mocked HTTP\"\"\"\n461:     ...\n462: \n463: @pytest.fixture\n464: def mock_data_plane():\n465:     \"\"\"Fixture for CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with mocked HTTP\"\"\"\n466:     ...\n467: \n468: @pytest.fixture\n469: def sample_session_response():\n470:     \"\"\"Fixture for session creation response\"\"\"\n471:     return {\"sessionId\": \"test-session-123\"}\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ### Test Coverage Goals\n475: - Client initialization: 90%+ coverage\n476: - Control plane operations: 85%+ coverage\n477: - Data plane operations: 85%+ coverage\n478: - Exception handling: 80%+ coverage\n479: - Utility functions: 90%+ coverage\n480: \n481: ---\n482: \n483: ## References\n484: \n485: - SDK source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/agentcube/`\n486: - Tests directory: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/tests/`\n487: - Package: `agentcube-sdk`\n488: - Dependencies: requests, PyJWT>=2.0.0, cryptography\n\n(End of file - total 488 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for testing the Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) and its CLI functionality.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-040\n- **Module**: `sdk-python/tests`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n## Reference\n\nBase specs from:\n- `python-sdk/design.md` - SDK design and architecture\n- `python-sdk/spec.md` - Functional requirements\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775884471523,"end":1775884471532}}}}
